<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,596,1051,1077]" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">
6. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Montagu, 1813)" baseAuthorityName="Montagu" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[179,596,1051,1077]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dexaminidae" genus="Dexamine" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[179,391,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">Dexamine spinosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Montagu, G." box="[406,588,1051,1077]" pageId="10" pageNumber="383" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref22466" refString="Montagu, G. (1813) Descriptions of several new or rare animals, principally marine, discovered on the South coast of Devonshire. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London, 11 (1), 1 - 26. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1813. tb 00035. x" type="journal article" year="1813">Montagu, 1813</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="383" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1123,1546]" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,397,1123,1149]" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">Materials examined.</emphasis>
43 individuals; Stations Vas. 2(8), 4(2), 5(4), 12(1), 13(1), 14(7), 18(1), 21(2), 23(6), 26(4), 30(1), 33(3), 36(2), 41(1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="383" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1123,1546]" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,305,1195,1221]" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">Distribution.</emphasis>
Atlanto-Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation author="Bellan-Santini, D. &amp; Ruffo, S." box="[589,930,1195,1221]" pageId="10" pageNumber="383" pagination="273 - 292" refId="ref18519" refString="Bellan-Santini, D. &amp; Ruffo, S. (2003) Biogeography of benthic marine amphipods in Mediterranean Sea. Biogeographia-The Journal of Integrative Biogeography, 24 (1), 273 - 292. https: // doi. org / 10.21426 / B 6110176" type="journal article" year="2003">Bellan-Santini &amp; Ruffo 2003</bibRefCitation>
). The species was reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[1317,1398,1195,1221]" name="Cyprus" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kocatas, A. &amp; Katagan, T." box="[198,434,1231,1258]" pageId="10" pageNumber="383" pagination="147 - 160" refId="ref20983" refString="Kocatas, A., Katagan, T. &amp; Huseyin. A. B. (2001) Contribution to the knowledge of the crustacean fauna of Cyprus. Israel Journal of Zoology, 47 (2), 147 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.1560 / YQL 8 - 4 PBT- 12 W 2 - 82 HV" type="journal article" year="2001">
Kocatas 
<emphasis box="[295,352,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">et al.</emphasis>
(2001)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Pavloudi, C. &amp; Christodoulou, M. &amp; Mavidis, M." box="[489,737,1231,1258]" pageId="10" pageNumber="383" pagination="8210" refId="ref23046" refString="Pavloudi, C., Christodoulou, M. &amp; Mavidis, M. (2016) Macrofaunal assemblages associated with the sponge Sarcotragus foetidus Schmidt, 1862 (Porifera: Demospongiae) at the coasts of Cyprus and Greece. Biodiversity Data Journal, 4, e 8210. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / BDJ. 4. e 8210" type="journal article" year="2016">
Pavloudi 
<emphasis box="[596,652,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
. In Vasiliko Bay (current study), it is considered as a common species (FI: 33.3 %).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="383" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1123,1546]" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,252,1303,1329]" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">Ecology.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[259,552,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">
Ecology. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Montagu" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[357,552,1304,1329]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dexaminidae" genus="Dexamine" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa">Dexamine spinosa</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
was found in association with algae, rocks and stones, soft bottom sediments (mud, mud-and mixture) at 
<quantity box="[423,518,1339,1366]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="15.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="383" unit="m" value="75.0" valueMax="150.0" valueMin="0.0">0–150 m</quantity>
depth (
<bibRefCitation author="Kocatas, A. &amp; Katagan, T." box="[598,805,1339,1365]" pageId="10" pageNumber="383" pagination="147 - 160" refId="ref20983" refString="Kocatas, A., Katagan, T. &amp; Huseyin. A. B. (2001) Contribution to the knowledge of the crustacean fauna of Cyprus. Israel Journal of Zoology, 47 (2), 147 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.1560 / YQL 8 - 4 PBT- 12 W 2 - 82 HV" type="journal article" year="2001">
Kocatas 
<emphasis box="[691,745,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">et al.</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
) and sponges 
<emphasis box="[957,966,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">(</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pavloudi, C. &amp; Christodoulou, M. &amp; Mavidis, M." box="[966,1184,1339,1366]" pageId="10" pageNumber="383" pagination="8210" refId="ref23046" refString="Pavloudi, C., Christodoulou, M. &amp; Mavidis, M. (2016) Macrofaunal assemblages associated with the sponge Sarcotragus foetidus Schmidt, 1862 (Porifera: Demospongiae) at the coasts of Cyprus and Greece. Biodiversity Data Journal, 4, e 8210. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / BDJ. 4. e 8210" type="journal article" year="2016">
Pavloudi 
<emphasis box="[1067,1120,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). In Vasiliko Bay it was found at depths of 
<quantity box="[398,479,1375,1402]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.95" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="0.4" pageId="10" pageNumber="383" unit="m" value="29.5" valueMax="55.0" valueMin="4.0">4–55 m</quantity>
(31 + 
<quantity box="[551,609,1375,1402]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="383" unit="m" value="15.0">15 m</quantity>
), mainly in muddy sand and also sand substrates, with organic matter ranging between 
<geoCoordinate box="[293,352,1411,1437]" degrees="2.446" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="10" pageNumber="383" precision="55" value="2.446">2.446</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[352,437,1411,1437]" degrees="11.119" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="10" pageNumber="383" precision="55" value="-11.119">–11.119</geoCoordinate>
% (6.538 + 2.482 %) and in association with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. V. Lamouroux" authorityYear="1809" baseAuthorityName="Forsskal" box="[920,1043,1411,1438]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Caulerpaceae" genus="Caulerpa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Bryopsidales" pageId="10" pageNumber="383" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="prolifera">
<emphasis box="[920,1043,1411,1438]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">C. prolifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sonder" authorityYear="1845" box="[1056,1211,1411,1438]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Caulerpaceae" genus="Caulerpa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Bryopsidales" pageId="10" pageNumber="383" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="cylindracea">
<emphasis box="[1056,1211,1411,1438]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">C. cylindracea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ascherson" authorityYear="1870" baseAuthorityName="Ucria" box="[1224,1332,1411,1438]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cymodoceaceae" genus="Cymodocea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alismatales" pageId="10" pageNumber="383" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nodosa">
<emphasis box="[1224,1332,1411,1438]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">C. nodosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Phaeophyceae" family="Dictyotaceae" genus="Dictyota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dictyotales" pageId="10" pageNumber="377" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="spp">
<emphasis box="[1345,1437,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">Dictyota</emphasis>
spp
</taxonomicName>
. and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ascherson" authorityYear="1867" baseAuthorityName="Forsskal" box="[292,432,1447,1473]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Bugulidae" genus="Halophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="10" pageNumber="383" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="stipulacea">
<emphasis box="[292,432,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="383">H. stipulacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It was found in stations classified according to the Bentix Index as in: “high” (1 station, 2 individuals), “good” (7 stations, 25 individuals) and “moderate” (6 stations, 16 individuals). It was recorded at the fish farm stations (12 individuals) and the power station outlet (2 individuals).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
